HEADWORD: Grama grass
<hw>Gra"ma grass`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Sp. <ets>grama</ets> a sort
of grass.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The name of several kinds of
pasture grasses found in the Western United States, esp. the
<spn>Bouteloua oligostachya</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

